****Command to open mysql
   mysql -u root -p
  p/w 123456789

*********Commands to install and configure redis server
$sudo apt-get update 
$sudo apt-get install redis-server
Start Redis
$redis-server
Check If Redis is Working
$redis-cli 
This will open a redis prompt.

redis 127.0.0.1:6379>



redis 127.0.0.1:6379> ping 
PONG
This shows that Redis is successfully installed on your machine.
*******************************
Getting Access of other database in Redis
 ssh ginger@192.168.0.231
p/w123456
